events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Jameis Winston threw for 325 yards and No. 3 Florida State rolled to a 41-14 victory against No. 7 Miami in another matchup of undefeated Atlantic Coast Conference rivals that turned into a Seminoles' blowout.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida St. sends Miami to first defeat

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: Doran Grant picked off Purdue's first pass, returning it for a touchdown, and Braxton Miller threw for 233 yards and four touchdowns Saturday as No. 4 Ohio State extended the nation's longest winning streak to 21 with a 56-0 rout at Purdue.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miller, Ohio State demolish Purdue

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd threw three touchdown passes and ran for a score and No. 8 Clemson broke the game open with three touchdowns in the last 4:18 of the first half in a 59-10 victory against Virginia on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boyd sets ACC TD record as Clemson rolls

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Maty Mauk threw three touchdown passes and ran for another, leading No. 10 Missouri's dominant and resilient effort in a 31-3 victory over Tennessee Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mizzou pounds Tennessee

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Tre Mason rushed for 168 yards and four touchdowns as No. 11 Auburn earned first-year coach Gus Malzahn a 35-17 win in his return to Arkansas.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mason guides No. 11 Auburn over Arkansas

events.name: UTEP Miners at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Johnny Manziel threw four touchdown passes and ran for two more scores in less than three quarters to lead No. 12 Texas A&M to a lopsided 57-7 win over UTEP on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Manziel's 6 TDs lift Aggies

events.name: Nevada Wolf Pack at Fresno State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Derek Carr threw for 487 yards to break the Fresno State career passing record and lead the 16th-ranked Bulldogs to eight straight wins to open the season for the first time since 1989 with a 41-23 victory over Nevada on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Carr throws for 487 yards as Fresno cruises

events.name: Northern Illinois Huskies at UMass Minutemen

headlines.description: Jordan Lynch ran for 119 yards and four touchdowns and threw for another in just over a half to lead No. 17 Northern Illinois to a 63-19 victory over Massachusetts on Saturday.

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Brett Hundley threw two touchdown passes and rushed for two more scores, Devin Fuller scored three touchdowns, and No. 17 UCLA shook off back-to-back losses with a 45-23 victory over Colorado on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 20 UCLA rebounds with win over Colorado

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Shilique Calhoun, Ed Davis and the rest of Michigan State's defense battered rival Michigan on Saturday, and the No. 22 Spartans remained unbeaten in the Big Ten with a 29-6 victory over the 21st-ranked Wolverines.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michigan State batters Michigan

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: James White ran for 132 yards and a pair of late touchdowns as 24th-ranked Wisconsin overwhelmed Iowa 28-9 on Saturday for its third straight win.

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Boston College Eagles

events.name: Temple Owls at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: — The season-opening game between Temple and Rutgers scheduled for Thursday night has been postponed until Saturday after the remnants of Hurricane Ida dumped historic rain over parts of the Northeast.
